[{"title":"DB2 Linux Install","key":"7718","dataProvider":null,"subtitle":"Install db2 on linux & unix","backgroundImage":"/images/00011943.gif","content":"<ul><li><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;color:#000000;\">Log in to the system with root authority i.e. username: root and your password</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;color:#000000;\">Change you directory to where you stored db2</span><br /></li></ul><pre class=\"pre codeblock\" style=\"background-color:#dadada;padding:5px;line-height:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:small;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;color:#000000;\">cd /dir</span></span></pre><ol></ol><ul><li><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;color:#000000;\">Download the tar image of db2 so to extract it you must use-</span></li></ul><pre class=\"pre codeblock\" style=\"background-color:#dadada;padding:5px;line-height:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:small;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;color:#000000;\">tar xvf product.tar</span></span></pre><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:small;line-height:1.5;font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;color:#000000;\">Change your directory&nbsp;</span></li></ul><pre class=\"pre codeblock\" style=\"background-color:#dadada;padding:5px;line-height:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:small;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;color:#000000;\">cd /dir/disk1</span></span></pre><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:small;line-height:normal;color:#000000;\">Enter the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"keyword cmdname\" style=\"font-weight:bold;font-size:small;line-height:normal;color:#000000;\">./db2setup</span><span style=\"font-size:small;line-height:normal;color:#000000;\">&nbsp;command from the directory where the product image resides to start the&nbsp;DB2 Setup&nbsp;wizard.</span><br /></li><li><span style=\"font-face:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal;font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;color:#000000;\">Installation Window opens where you can click on Install New. It then obvious from then where you can install db2.&nbsp;</span></span></li></ul><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Things to remember while using DB2 on Linux:</span></strong></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">1. Whenever you are using DB2 on linux, always remember to add the command like this: db2 “&lt;your-db2-command&gt;” as on linux there are several commands which the linux machine will interpret as a linux command and not a db2 command. Hence its best to keep the query inside double quotes.</span></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">2. Always start the database manager by db2start as sometimes we wonder why the query is not working</span></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">3. If anything goes wrong with db2 then make your changes and restart db2 but first stop it.</span></p><p></p><p></p>","type":"articlefeature","param1":null,"param2":null,"description":"DB2 Setup wizard on Linux and UNIX operating systems","url":null,"id":null,"providerid":null,"hideimage":false,"maxitems":0,"likesno":0,"commentsno":0,"date":"0001-01-01T00:00:00"},{"title":"Database Manager","key":"7719","dataProvider":null,"subtitle":"Start/Stop DB Manager","backgroundImage":"/images/00000520.gif","content":"<p></p><p>Database Manager is the manager of the database which runs like a instance or several instances. The best way to check if db2 is installed correctly or not is to check if the database manager is running. That would the most basic and first step to get to.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\">The few commands which every user using DB2 will require. These are the list of commands:</p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">1. Start the database manager and enter the db2 command line</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0px 0px 1.5em 3em;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;list-style-position:initial;list-style-image:initial;color:#666666;\"><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><strong>db2start:</strong> This command will help you start the database manager. Sometimes we just start typing db2 commands and wonder why they are not working then this can be one of the reasons why the command is not working.db2start</li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><strong>db2:</strong> By this you enter the db2 prompt, where all your commands will be db2 so you do not have to append db2 in the beginning. For example:&nbsp;db2 start</li></ul><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">2. Stop the database manager</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0px 0px 1.5em 3em;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;list-style-position:initial;list-style-image:initial;color:#666666;\"><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><strong>db2stop:</strong> This will stop the database manager</li></ul><p><br /></p>","type":"article","param1":null,"param2":null,"description":"Learn about the db2 database manager","url":null,"id":null,"providerid":null,"hideimage":false,"maxitems":0,"likesno":0,"commentsno":0,"date":"0001-01-01T00:00:00"},{"title":"Connect & Disconnect Database","key":"7720","dataProvider":null,"subtitle":"Connecting and disconnecting db from server","backgroundImage":"/images/Untitled11.png","content":"<p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">&nbsp;</strong></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">Create database<br style=\"line-height:inherit;\" /></strong></p><ul style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0px 0px 1.5em 3em;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;list-style-position:initial;list-style-image:initial;color:#666666;\"><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">db2 “CREATE DATABASE &lt;DB-NAME&gt;”</li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">This is help u create a database</li></ul><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">Create table</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0px 0px 1.5em 3em;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;list-style-position:initial;list-style-image:initial;color:#666666;\"><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">db2 “CREATE TABLE &lt;table-name&gt; COL1 DATATYPE”</li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">This creates the table for you in db2</li></ul><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">Drop database/table</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0px 0px 1.5em 3em;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;list-style-position:initial;list-style-image:initial;color:#666666;\"><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">db2 “DROP DATABASE &lt;db-name&gt;</li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">db2 “DROP TABLE &lt;table-name&gt;</li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">The above 2 commands will help you drop database or table</li></ul><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">List all databases/nodes<br style=\"line-height:inherit;\" /></strong></p><ul style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0px 0px 1.5em 3em;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;list-style-position:initial;list-style-image:initial;color:#666666;\"><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">list db directory</li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">This command list all the databases in the system and their nodes, alias name, local database directory.</li></ul><p></p>","type":"article","param1":null,"param2":null,"description":"This step will teach you how to connect a db and how to disconnect a db as well as creating a database.","url":null,"id":null,"providerid":null,"hideimage":false,"maxitems":0,"likesno":0,"commentsno":0,"date":"0001-01-01T00:00:00"},{"title":"DB Manager Configuration","key":"7721","dataProvider":null,"subtitle":"details about configurations of db2","backgroundImage":"/images/gv_DB2LUWInstanceHousingCollectionOfDatabasesSharingSameEngineAndDa_tadm7fd9.png","content":"<h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" style=\"font-size:1.2em;margin-bottom:0em;padding-bottom:0em;margin-top:1em;word-spacing:0.1em;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;line-height:normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Command syntax</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><img alt=\"Read syntax diagram\" border=\"0\" longdesc=\"http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/db2luw/v9r5/topic/com.ibm.db2.luw.admin.cmd.doc/doc/r0001955syn1.html\" src=\"http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/db2luw/v9r5/topic/com.ibm.db2.luw.admin.cmd.doc/c.gif\" /></span><a href=\"http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/db2luw/v9r5/topic/com.ibm.db2.luw.admin.cmd.doc/doc/r0001955.html#d96367e72\" style=\"color:#996699;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><img alt=\"Skip visual syntax diagram\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/db2luw/v9r5/topic/com.ibm.db2.luw.admin.cmd.doc/c.gif\" /></span></a><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"> &gt;&gt;-GET--+-DATABASE MANAGER-+--+-CONFIGURATION-+--+-------------+-&gt;&lt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; +-DB MANAGER-------+ +-CONFIG--------+ '-SHOW DETAIL-'&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; '-DBM--------------' '-CFG-----------' &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"></span></p><p></p><dt class=\"dt dlterm\" style=\"margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;line-height:normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">SHOW DETAIL</span></dt><p></p><ul><li><dt class=\"dt dlterm\" style=\"margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;line-height:normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong>Displays detailed information showing the current value of database manager configuration parameters as well as the value of the parameters the next time you start the database manager. This option lets you see the result of dynamic changes to configuration parameters</strong>.<br /></span></dt></li><li><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Once you enter the above command, you will get a big list. It would be difficult to explain everything and as you keep getting these various experiences you will learn about it. But the most common and must know about the config is:</span></li></ul><p><strong style=\"font-size:0.75em;line-height:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:small;\">diaglevel </span></strong><span style=\"font-size:small;line-height:1.5;font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">- Diagnostic error capture level configuration parameter</span></p><ul><li><dt class=\"dt dlterm\" style=\"margin-top:0.5em;margin-bottom:0.5em;font-weight:bold;\">Default [range]</dt><dd class=\"dd\" style=\"margin-left:1em;\">[0-4]</dd></li></ul><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:1em;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;line-height:normal;\"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Valid values for this parameter are:</strong></p><ul class=\"ul\" style=\"margin-top:0.1em;padding-top:0.1em;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;line-height:normal;\"><li class=\"li\" style=\"margin-top:0em;margin-bottom:0em;margin-left:0em;\"><strong class=\"ph b\">0</strong>&nbsp;– Only critical errors, event messages, and administration notification messages are captured on the server side. You cannot set the value of this parameter to&nbsp;<span class=\"keyword option\">0</span>&nbsp;on the client side.</li><li class=\"li\" style=\"margin-top:0em;margin-bottom:0em;margin-left:0em;\"><strong class=\"ph b\">1</strong>&nbsp;– Only severe errors, critical errors, event messages, and administration notification messages are captured.</li><li class=\"li\" style=\"margin-top:0em;margin-bottom:0em;margin-left:0em;\"><strong class=\"ph b\">2</strong>&nbsp;– All errors, event messages, and administration notification messages are captured.</li><li class=\"li\" style=\"margin-top:0em;margin-bottom:0em;margin-left:0em;\"><strong>3</strong> – All errors, warnings, event messages, and administration notification messages are captured.</li><li class=\"li\" style=\"margin-top:0em;margin-bottom:0em;margin-left:0em;\"><strong class=\"ph b\">4</strong>&nbsp;– All errors, warnings, informational messages, event messages, and administration notification messages are captured.</li></ul><p></p><p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><br /></span></p><p><br /></p><p></p>","type":"article","param1":null,"param2":null,"description":"This step will teach you about the most important topic on configurations of db2. Most ignore it but when everything stops working then this is the place you want to be.","url":null,"id":null,"providerid":null,"hideimage":false,"maxitems":0,"likesno":0,"commentsno":0,"date":"0001-01-01T00:00:00"},{"title":"Technology Explorer","key":"7722","dataProvider":null,"subtitle":"the best UI for ibm db2","backgroundImage":"/images/Untitled6.png","content":"<p></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\">Technology Explorer is the best software I know for IBM DB2. It has a simple user interface where even an immature can go and learn db2. It is easy to use and has built-in tutorials for any one who does not know how to use it will help you learn more about it. We all know the efficiency of IBM DB2 and its uses. It is a open source IBM software. Anyone who wants to learn db2 can learn how to use it. It is a web based console but requires IBM DB2 driver and php for it. If you want to learn db2 basics or become an expert in DB2 then Tech Explorer is the web console you definitely want to learn.</p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\">It uses XML for querying the database and has features to auto-generate the xml for you so that it makes your code easier. It is a light weight console hence any browser supports TE. In TE, there are tutorials where you learn how to customize the interface, write ad-hoc sql query, etc. You can even create tutorials for others to use TE. It is that kind of tool where you can tweak the way you want to. The most strong point of Tech Explorer is its quick results and efficiency. You just have to connect to the database by giving the connection information and you are good to go. It teaches you the core features of db2.</p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\">Personally I would prefer Tech Explorer for db2 better than any other web console.</p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">Requirements:</strong></p><ol style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0px 0px 1.5em 3em;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;list-style-position:initial;list-style-image:initial;color:#666666;\"><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><a href=\"http://www-01.ibm.com/software/data/db2/express/\" style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#ff8f85;text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.3s linear;-webkit-transition:all 0.3s linear;\" target=\"_blank\">DB2</a></li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><a href=\"http://webdeveloperankitakulkarni.wordpress.com/httpd.apache.org/\" style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#ff8f85;text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.3s linear;-webkit-transition:all 0.3s linear;\" target=\"_blank\">Apache HTTP Server</a></li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><a href=\"http://www.php.net/\" style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#ff8f85;text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.3s linear;-webkit-transition:all 0.3s linear;\" target=\"_blank\">PHP 5.2.x</a></li><li style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\"><a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/db2mc/files/\" style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#ff8f85;text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.3s linear;-webkit-transition:all 0.3s linear;\" target=\"_blank\">IBM_DB2 PHP Driver</a></li></ol><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">In order to download Tech Explorer:</strong></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">Go to this website:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/db2mc/\" style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#ff8f85;text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.3s linear;-webkit-transition:all 0.3s linear;\">Link</a></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\">I am pretty sure that I must have convinced you enough for using Tech Explorer.</p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\"><strong style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\">Do you want to learn more about Tech Explorer:</strong></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\">Go here:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/db2mc/files/Documentation/TEGettingStarted.pdf/download\" style=\"line-height:inherit;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-style:inherit;margin:0px;outline:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#ff8f85;text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.3s linear;-webkit-transition:all 0.3s linear;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Getting Started\">Getting Started</a></p><p style=\"line-height:23px;border:0px;font-family:Muli, 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', Verdana, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:1.5em;outline:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-left:0px;vertical-align:baseline;color:#666666;\">I am completely impressed by the use of Tech Explorer and would recommend everyone to use it.&nbsp;If you have any questions in terms of Tech Explorer or db2, I will be happy to answer them.</p><p></p>","type":"articlesmall","param1":null,"param2":null,"description":"This software for db2 is the most light-weight and user-friendly UI of IBM db2.","url":null,"id":null,"providerid":null,"hideimage":false,"maxitems":0,"likesno":0,"commentsno":0,"date":"0001-01-01T00:00:00"},{"title":"Cataloging/Uncataloging Databases","key":"7723","dataProvider":null,"subtitle":"Catalog/Uncatalog db","backgroundImage":"/images/images (1).jpg","content":"<p></p><strong><span style=\"font-face:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><div class=\"gmail_default\" style=\"display:inline;\"><p>db2 catalog tcpip node &lt;pick-a-node-name&gt; remote &lt;ip-addr-of-remote-system&gt; server &lt;port-of-db2-inst-on-remote-<wbr></wbr>machine&gt;<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Database: </p><p>CATALOG DATABASE &lt;database-you-want&gt; AS &lt;db-name-on-local-machine&gt; AT NODE &lt;node-you-catalogued&gt; AUTHENTICATION SERVER</p><p></p><strong><span style=\"font-face:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><div class=\"gmail_default\" style=\"display:inline;\">Uncataloging:<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Node:&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; db2 uncatalog node &lt;nodename&gt;<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Database:&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; db2 uncatalog db &lt;db-alias&gt;</div></span></strong><p></p></div></span></strong><p></p>","type":"articlesmall","param1":null,"param2":null,"description":"Learn how to catalog i.e. attach db to a node and uncatalog i.e.detach db from the node","url":null,"id":null,"providerid":null,"hideimage":false,"maxitems":0,"likesno":0,"commentsno":0,"date":"0001-01-01T00:00:00"},{"title":" PHP - DB2","key":"7724","dataProvider":null,"subtitle":"How to use db2 with php","backgroundImage":"/images/images (2).jpg","content":"<p><a href=\"http://pear.php.net/package/PEAR/download\" style=\"color:#1155cc;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p><p><strong>Download the PEAR package</strong></p><p><a href=\"http://pear.php.net/package/PEAR/download\" style=\"color:#1155cc;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" target=\"_blank\">http://pear.php.net/package/<wbr></wbr>PEAR/download</a><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"color:#222222;font-face:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal;\"><strong>Download the DB2 driver required for PHP</strong></span></span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><a href=\"http://pecl.php.net/package/ibm_db2\" style=\"color:#1155cc;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" target=\"_blank\">http://pecl.php.net/package/<wbr></wbr>ibm_db2<br /><br /></a><span style=\"font-size:small;\">Requires&nbsp;</span>a db2 driver for php. This driver connects php with db2. Without this, none of this works.</p><p><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\"><strong>Prereq:</strong> </span></p><p><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">I've installed DB2, Apache and php)</span><br /><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Download the file: ibm_db2-1.8.2.tgz</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Untar the file: tar -xvf ibm_db2-1.8.2.tgz</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Go to the main directory</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Execute 'phpize' and that creates several files.</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Execute './configure --with-IBM_DB2=/opt/ibmn/db2/</span><wbr style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\"></wbr><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">V9.5_01'</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Execute 'make'</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Execute 'make install'</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">- Modify the php.ini file in order to activate the ibm_db2.so extension.</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; extension=ibm_db2.so</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">To check that the library is included: php -i</span><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><br style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\" /><span style=\"color:#222222;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:small;line-height:normal;\">Then, you have to restart Apache: httpd -k restart</span></p>","type":"articlesmall","param1":null,"param2":null,"description":"We need a setup before using db2 with php. Want to know? Learn how?","url":null,"id":null,"providerid":null,"hideimage":false,"maxitems":0,"likesno":0,"commentsno":0,"date":"0001-01-01T00:00:00"}]